Brazil Current Account Deficit Narrows to $3.5 Billion in April

-- B y   M a t t h e w   B r i s t o w
-- 
2011-05-25T13:34:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/brazil-current-account-deficit-narrows-to-3-5-billion-in-april.html
Brazil  posted a $3.5 billion current
account deficit in April, the central bank said.  The deficit, the broadest measure of trade in goods and
services, compares with a $5.7 billion deficit in March, the
bank said today in report released in Brasilia.  Foreign direct investment was $5.5 billion in April,
compared with $6.8 billion in March, the bank said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Matthew Bristow in Brasilia at 
 mbristow5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
